title: For Sale:  BM
postcontent: The MRAD rifle's user-changeable barrel system is just one example of this hardworking gun's modularity. Available in .338 Lapua Magnum, .300 Winchester Magnum and .308 Winchester, the precision grade barrel can be removed by simply loosening two bolts using a standard Torx wrench. Besides reducing maintenance and logistical burdens, this unique design allows for user level caliber interchangeability and serviceability with the MRAD rifle's barrel kits. The MRAD also boasts Barrett's fully adjustable match-grade trigger module, which is user accessible. The thumb-operated safety can be configured for left or right hand operation. The ambidextrous magazine release can be used intuitively while retaining a firing grip and cheek weld. Integrated into the MRAD rifle's 7000 series aluminum upper receiver is a 21.75 inch M1913 rail with 20 MOA taper. The forward receiver is drilled and tapped for accessory rails to be mounted at the 3, 6 and 9 o'clock positions. The MRAD stock is foldable for enhanced portability yet locks in as solid as a fixed-stock rifle, creating a rigid platform for consistent firing. During transport the stock folds and locks onto the bolt handle maintaining the same rifle width whether folded or extended. Made of a temperature-resistant polymer, the adjustable cheek piece also offers a consistent rifle-to-user contact point. The rifle's length of pull can be set to five different positions with the push of a single button. From its quick-detach sling mounts to the Barrett Multi-Role Brown color that blends into any environment - every detail of the MRAD has been carefully designed to create one thing: a high-performance rifle you can truly make your own. Mounted on this rifle from the factory with Barrett rings is a Leupold Mk 4 4.5-14x50 long range riflescope. The Leupold sports a 30mm main tube, mil dot reticle, and M1 turrets. Rifle with two 10-rnd mags, 2 rail sections with flush cup mounts, and one plain railed section.

It has a made in Japan 10x42 adjustable to distance/focus SWFA Classic "Super Sniper" Scope. This scope was made by the company that made the Bausch and Laumb Elite series scope for Bushnell. title: For Sale:  HK G3 OLD STYLE COLLAPSIBLE STOCK - SHOOTERS STOCK
postcontent:
First generation HK G3 collapsible stock made by Heckler and Koch in Oberndorf Germany. These old style stocks are the way to go for civilian shooters. Later versions used a reversed angle buttpad, which worked great for launching rifled grenades off the ground, but dramatically increased felt recoil off the shoulder.

If you love the look of the collapsible stock, but don't want the big increase in felt recoil, this is the stock for you.

HK G3 Collapsible Stocks will fit all HK91/G3 rifles and clones including the PTR91, FMP, SAR3/8* and the Cetme.

I paid 300 plus tax and shipping, offered at a loss at 250 bucks.  have a great day!

title: For Sale:  Marlin 336 Lever-Action .30-30 Rifle, Redfield Scope, Ammo
postcontent:
I'm selling my Marlin Model 336 lever-action .30-30 rifle.  I no longer hunt, so the rifle has not been fired in at least 10 years.  The serial number indicates it was built in 1982, back when there was some real quality and workmanship in guns.  The gun is in excellent condition, with some very minor wear and marks from use over the years.

It is fitted with a Redfield 1.75 x 5 Wide-Field scope, very appropriate for this gun.  The scope was factory-overhauled in 2005.  I have the paperwork that shows the work accomplished.  They are great scopes, clear, hold their zero and durable.  It's by far the best scope for someone who can't use open sights or peep sights but likes to still hunt.

There is also included an attractive padded leather sling, attached to the rifle with quick-detachable swivels.

Marlin’s Model 336 is a high quality tube-fed repeating lever-action rifle that has been around since 1948.  Since its introduction, over 6 million Model 336 rifles have been produced. It continues to be one of the most popular and common rifles in the USA.  They are well-built, accurate, robust, and reliable. One of the key selling points of the model 336 is that they have a solid receiver top, giving the rifle extra strength and allowing for side ejection.  The solid top of the model 336 supplies a platform to easily mount an optic sight.  

Another outstanding feature of the model 336 is that it’s designed to be easily disassembled for cleaning inside the barrel. Unscrewing the lever pivot screw allows removal of the lever arm, bolt, and ejector for maintenance. 

To complete this package, I have a many-years' supply of ammunition, plus dies and components for reloading more.  Here is a listing of the .30-30 ammo:

3 boxes Seirra 150 gr. flat-nose .30-30 bullets

This package will put you in the .30-30 business for years to come.  The 32 boxes of ammo will allow practice and many years of hunting.  I'm expecting to get $795 for the gun, scope, accessories and ammo.  Have you priced ammo lately?
